status_message:
There are three phrases that I learned growing up that need to be drummed into the brains of every person in this country.

1. "Sticks and Stones can break my bones, but words will never hurt me." Being bullied sucks. Been there done that. Until they lay a hand on you, you just have to toughen up and ignore them. Once they lay a hand on you, THEN you can physically retaliate. I never had to get physical with the same bully twice.

2. "Your right to swing your fist ends where my nose begins". Other people have rights too and as long as they aren't actually hurting you, you DO NOT have the right to try and stop them.

3. "I may not agree with what you're saying, but I'll defend to the death your right to say it." If you're not willing to defend someone else's rights, you should have no reasonable expectation of keeping your own.

If more American followed those three simple principles, this country would be a much better place. There would be no more PC censorship, no more idiotic lawsuits over stupidity, people could serve who they wished, and people would simply have to learn to deal with reality. Not everyone is going to like you. The world isn't "Fair" and using the courts to impose your will on someone else isn't fair either because you are taking away THEIR rights.
The question is did this host inform Kelly this line of questioning would take place before the interview...

status_message:
Thanksgiving #NinjaBeef

2-3 lbs beef tips
2 cans cream/celery
4-5 lg red potatoes
1 large onion (red)

Montreal steak seasoning
1 crockpot

Cut up all your potatoes and line bottom of crockpot with them. Lay your beef tips on top until you see no more potatoes. Cut up your onion and place on top of your beef tips. Sprinkle Montreal Steak Season all over the top of onions and beef. Spread cream of celery over the beef tips, onions and seasoning. 

Make sure you can't see any beef or onions.

Set your crockpot on low for eight hours. Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

NOTE: You won't need water because the beef makes it's own liquid for gravy. 

Have fun

In honor of the 44th President of the United States, Baskin-Robbins Ice Cream has introduced a new flavor: "Barocky Road."

Barocky Road is a blend of half vanilla, half chocolate, and surrounded by nuts and flakes. The vanilla portion of the mix is not openly advertised and usually denied as an ingredient. The nuts and flakes are all very bitter and hard to swallow.

The cost is $92.84 per scoop...so out of a hundred dollar bill you are at least promised some CHANGE..!

When purchased it will be presented to you in a large beautiful cone, but after you pay for it, the ice cream is taken away and given to the person in line behind you at no charge.

You are left with an almost empty wallet, staring at an empty cone and wondering what just happened. Then you realize this is what "redistribution of wealth" is all about.

Aren't you just stimulated?

BOOM Trey Gowdy Now is in the ROOM
BREAKING: Trey Gowdy Announces Plan to Speed Up Deportation, DESTROY Obama's AMNESTY!
When it comes to defending the Constitution and keeping America safe, we're seeing way too many Republicans unwilling to fight. But Rep. Trey Gowdy (S-SC), a conservative hero and a legendary former prosecutor, is tough as nails‚Ä¶ And he just announced his plan to stop Obama!
Gowdy just introduced an immigration bill which would not only speed up deportations, but it would completely wipe out Barack Obama's illegal executive orders on amnesty. Yes!
Named after Michael Davis, Jr., a sheriff's deputy in California who was killed in the line of duty last year by an illegal immigrant, Gowdy's bill would also provide a work-around for state and local governments to reinforce federal immigration laws while also implementing an annual review of the executive branch's use of prosecutorial discretion in immigration cases.
"If we are serious about finding a long term solution to our immigration system, we must address interior enforcement," Gowdy, the Republican chairman of the Immigration and Border Security Subcommittee, said in a statement announcing the measure.
"This bill, which is one part of the Committee's step-by-step process to address our broken immigration system, will ensure we do not repeat the mistakes of the past and help us earn back the trust of the American public," he added.
If enacted, the bill would completely dismantle what Gowdy describes as Obama's "unilateral, constitutional actions on immigration" by cutting off any and all funds to the initiative. It would also strip Obama and all future presidents of any power to unilaterally shut down immigration enforcement by allowing state and local governments the authorization to enforce federal immigration laws.
via The Daily Caller
America can not wait until the next Presidential election to secure the Southern border. Gowdy's plan is fearless and necessary, as the border is not secure.

status_message:
THANK YOU TO EVERYONE THAT HAS GIVEN EITHER THROUGH DONATIONS OR PRAYERS! 

Unlike my regular posts, this is not politics. It's personal.

This past week, my family found itself in a situation that both overwhelmed me and made me reach out in a very personal and public way to ask for assistance.

ORIGINAL POST ‚û° EMERGENCY‚Ä¶‚Ä¶I NEED YOUR HELP IMMEDIATELY! http://newsninja2012.com/emergency-i-need-your-help-immediately

In a very real way, I had to set aside the pride I have in being a man who takes care of his family to seek help in providing some very critical things for them. Growing up, I remember hearing an evangelist speak on how men often behave. Most of the time, men do not seek assistance for themselves. Even going to the doctor is pushed off with self assurance that the pain will subside in a few hours or days.

Asking for emotional and financial help is often even harder for men who want to be seen as the hero and provider to their family.  Most often a man wants to tell his spouse, loved one, girlfriend, or child "Everything will be alright, I got this." When you see a man put his head in his partner's chest and say "Babe, we're in trouble," that's when things are about to hit the fan. It's hard to ask for help in those times because as men we don't want to rely on assistance, which we feel might make us look weak.

Consistent with my Conservative philosophies I work hard to make progress on my own merit and talents, rather than leaning on the government to subsidize my family or my responsibilities. I have always taken care of my family and made sure they had what they needed. I take a lot of pride in my family, children and the opportunities I have been able to provide for them until now.

I didn't open up my life to the masses about my personal situation because I have been taking care of things by myself. We all face good and bad times in our lives and if fortunate, there are more good times. I believe what defines us is how we deal with the challenges we face. I continue to work hard everyday in my role as an activist trying to improve our government and political system. I also am relentless in trying to reclaim a role as a productive member of the economy as I always have been. My family will get through this and be the better for it but for now God's will be done and we don't question what he has in store for us. Our faith is unshaken.

For this reason, my family and I want to thank the people that were able to help with donations and prayers following the accident involving my wife and son yesterday. Both are home and healing and for that we are blessed. We are trying to answer everyone who has contacted us personally but wanted our gratitude and thanks to touch everyone who helped pass the message and sent quick and silent well wishes. This is an amazing community of people and I thank God for every one of you.

God Bless

Wayne

status_message:
When progressives tell you the parties switched, fight back that lie with facts and don't waver because history is on your side.

* Republicans enacted civil rights laws in the 1950's and 1960's, over the objection of Democrats.

* Republicans founded the HBCU's (Historical Black College's and Universities) and started the NAACP to counter the racist practices of the Democrats.

* Republicans pushed through much of the ground-breaking civil rights legislation in Congress.

* Republicans fought slavery and amended the Constitution to grant blacks freedom, citizenship and the right to vote.

* Republicans pushed through much of the groundbreaking civil rights legislation from the 1860s through the 1960s.

* Republican President Dwight Eisenhower sent troops into the South to desegregate the schools.

* Republican President Eisenhower appointed Chief Justice Earl Warren to the Supreme Court, which resulted in the 1954 Brown vs. Board of Education decision.

* Republican Senator Everett Dirksen from Illinois, not Democrat President Lyndon Johnson, was the one who pushed through the civil rights laws of the 1960's.

* Republican Senator Everett Dirksen from Illinois wrote the language for the 1965 Voting Rights Act.

* Republican Senator Everett Dirksen from Illinois also crafted the language for the Civil Rights Act of 1968 which prohibited discrimination in housing.

* Republican and black American, A. Phillip Randolph, organized the 1963 March by Dr. King on Washington.

* The 1964 Civil Rights Act Roll Call Vote: In the House, only 64 percent of the Democrats (153 yes, 91 no), but 80 percent of the Republicans (136 yes, 35 no), voted for it. In the Senate, while only 68 percent of the Democrats endorsed the bill (46 yes, 21 no), 82 percent of the Republicans voted to enact it (27 yes, 6 no).
